      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's just so hard to care about resilience or little things when the weight of it all feels so permanent. everything feels so stagnant. like i'm just stuck in this loop of grief that has no exit. honestly, sometimes it feels less like i'm waiting for him and more like i'm just waiting for the end of it all. it's just so much easier to imagine the silence being final than it is to imagine living through another forty years of this emptiness.",
      "source": "evaluator"
